==English==
===Abbreviation===
a cripple
:'''Straight crip,''' actually crippled or otherwise afflicted. '''Phoney crip,''' self-mutilated or simulating a deformity.--"A No. 1" ''Mother Delcassee of Hoboes'' (1918) 84

:'''Crip,''' a crippled animal.--Lester Berrey & Melvin Van Den Bark ''The American Thesaurus of Slang'' (1942) §120/2

:He only loved people, he thought, who had fought or been mutilated... So I'm a sucker for crips, he thought.--Ernest Hemingway ''Across the River and into the Trees'' (1950) viii. 62